As configured in AWS Linux, cloud-init runs the user-data script in the root user account, so when you explicitly modify `/home/ec2-user/.bashrc`, then source `~/.bashrc` you&#39;re talking about two different `.bashrc` files.

I&#39;d suggest explicitly sourcing the `.bashrc` file in the `ec2-user` folder.  Or, you can add something like this to the top of your script to switch the context to the `ec2-user` user if it&#39;s been run as root:

```bash
#!/bin/bash

if [ $UID -eq 0 ]; then
  sudo chmod 777 &quot;$0&quot;
  exec su ec2-user &quot;$0&quot;
fi
```

